<plot>Before her first individual exhibition, a young artist unveils her drawings to her friend, the filmmaker. The work process, her visual sensibility and the categories of drawing - line, stain and mark - are assembled cinematographically in a intuitive manner. Her performative drawing, her theoretical stance, both are set in motion in a zoo - where uncanny and inspiring subjects roam untamed.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?012581</url></doc>
